GCOutbound

public GCOutbound(int dxdev,
                  long linedev,
                  java.lang.String destination,
                  java.lang.String origin)
           throws JVRException
Constructs a GCOutbound object that will drive a call to the specified number.

Parameters:
dxdev - A voice device handle to use.
linedev - A valid Global Call line device handle.
destination - The phone number to connect to.
origin - The phone number that is provided for caller ID (the number *doing* the calling).
Method Detail

start

public void start()
           throws JVRException
After initialization, call this method to start dialing. This method calls gc.ResetLineDev(long, long) to make certain that the line device is NULL/IDLE. It also primes the event handling mechanisms.

Throws:
JVRException

                                  long linedev,
                                  java.lang.String destination,
                                  java.lang.String origin,
                                  long timeout,
                                  DX_CAP cap,
                                  java.lang.String protocol)
                           throws JVRException
Synchronous function.

Parameters:
dxdev - Voice device handle to use when doing CAP.
linedev - Global call line device handle to use to make the call.
destination - Destination phone number.
origin - Origin (calling party number).
timeout - Time in milliseconds before the call is aborted.
protocol - The Global Call protocol that was used to open the line device.
Returns:
The instance of GCOutbound that was used to make the call.
